table-0304-560.pgTitle: List of riots and civil unrest in Calgary
table-0304-560.caption: Events
data: [218th_(Edmonton)_Battalion,_CEF|218th Battalion of the Canadian Expeditionary Force]
Soldiers from the former 218th Battalion of the CEF rioted in Calgary after being ordered to depart immediately for Europe. They attacked 14 stores, restaurants and cafes throughout the city.
300 protesters with the Central Council of the Unemployed marched on City Hall for "relief" in the form of places to sleep, food to eat and transportation to work sites.

The Calgary Urban Treaty Indian Alliance held a demonstration over social service funding in which dozens of men, women and children occupied the Indian Affairs office in the city. Government officials labeled the participants "terrorists". The local papers charged the protesters with "public mischief" and civil infractions. While charges were not lodged against demonstrators, several reported increased government discrimination against them afterward.

1 death — A tornado moved northeast through an industrial section of Grenada, missing a hospital by only yards (ft). Most of the $300,000 in damage was confined to a plywood-box factory, though the tornado also hit 23 homes.

1 death — A tornado killed numerous chickens and destroyed at least 12 homes and 12 barns.
